The paper discusses the relationship between the symmetric Laplacian of a graph and a bipartite quantum state, suggesting a connection to quantum information theory (cs.IT) and quantum computing (quant-ph). It also studies extreme values for the R\'enyi-$p$ entropy of graphs, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the Von Neumann entropy, which is a measure of information entropy commonly used in information theory and signal processing (cs.SI).
